---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import DefaultLayout from '../layouts/DefaultLayout.astro';
import { loadBounties } from '../lib/data';

const programs = loadBounties();
const count = programs.length;
---

<DefaultLayout title="About - Bug Bounties" description="About the Bug Bounties directory - how data is collected and how to contribute.">
  <Header />
  <article class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>What is this?</h2>
      <p>
        Bug Bounties is an open-source directory of <strong>{count.toLocaleString()}</strong> bug bounty
        and responsible disclosure programs. It helps security researchers quickly find companies
        that welcome vulnerability reports.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How is data collected?</h2>
      <p>
        Program data is aggregated from multiple public sources, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>HackerOne</li>
        <li>Bugcrowd</li>
        <li>Intigriti</li>
        <li>YesWeHack</li>
        <li>Federacy</li>
        <li>Disclose.io</li>
        <li>security.txt files</li>
        <li>Manual submissions via GitHub</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Data is refreshed periodically via automated workflows and community contributions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How to contribute</h2>
      <p>
        This project is open-source. You can add or update programs by submitting a pull request
        to the <a href="https://github.com/Lissy93/bug-bounties">GitHub repository</a>.
        Each entry is stored in <code>bounties.yml</code> and follows a defined schema.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Responsible disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        If you find a vulnerability in one of these programs, always follow their specific
        disclosure policy. General guidance:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Read the program's rules before testing</li>
        <li>Only test on systems you are authorized to test</li>
        <li>Do not access, modify, or delete user data</li>
        <li>Report vulnerabilities promptly and provide enough detail to reproduce</li>
        <li>Give the company reasonable time to fix before any public disclosure</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Credits and license</h2>
      <p>
        Built by <a href="https://aliciasykes.com">Alicia Sykes</a>.
        Licensed under <a href="https://github.com/Lissy93/bug-bounties/blob/main/LICENSE">MIT</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</DefaultLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    width: var(--content-width);
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }
  .about h1 {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-size: 2rem;
  }
  section {
    background: var(--background-lighter);
    border-radius: var(--curve);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--primary);
  }
  p {
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--primary);
  }
  code {
    background: var(--background-darker);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: var(--curve);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
